This is a '''timeline of [[healthcare in Ethiopia]]''', focusing especially on modern science-based medicine healthcare. Major events such as policies and organizations are described.
==Big picture== {| class="sortable wikitable" ! Year/period !! Key developments |- |Prior to 1896||Local [[traditional African medicine]] is present in Ethiopia for most of its history. |- |1896–onward||Western medicine is consolidated after first hospital is built by Europeans.<ref name="Ethiopia’s Physician Brain-Drain Problem; What to Do?" /> |- |1948–onward||The Ministry of Health is established.<ref name="Ethiopia’s Physician Brain-Drain Problem; What to Do?" /> |- |Present||Today, the major health problems of Ethiopia remain largely preventable communicable diseases and nutritional disorders. The rate of morbidity and mortality remain high and the health status is relatively poor. Physician [[brain drain]] is an actual major issue.<ref name="Ethiopia’s Physician Brain-Drain Problem; What to Do?" /> |- |}
